Michal:
That kind of error sometimes can happen when you are missing a few plugins in your launch configuration.
There also has been some dependency reduction that was applied following bug 161171 
Could you check still if there are validation errors in the plugins tab of your launch configuration? (button is validate plugin set)
And make sure the clear configuration flag is checked on the config tab?

Could you also double check that build automatically is checked in the project menu?
It is possible that you have the plugin part of your launch conf, yet that the class was not compiled if build is not tunred on. Hence depiste the bundle would be resolved by OSGI, the class would not be found when you launch the runtime workbench.
I am saying that because I was able to reproduce the exact same stack trace as you, by disabling the auto build, and deleting the compiled MozillaCloseWindowListener class file.
So there must be something similar going on in your setup.
